  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of health care and medical services for the vulnerable groups of IDPs and hosting community residing in AlHamam,AlFied and AlBasah  , Lattakia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lattakia, the city which is holding a huge responsibility for 6 years because it provided shelter and security for every refugee from other areas in Syria.
This governorate is experiencing severe health challenges under the current deteriorated situation in Syria.

This project will provide medical care to the poor and IDPs in Lattakia,  and will target patients in need for hospitalization and tertiary care of which most of them are from most vulnerable groups (IDPs, women) who can&#x2019;t afford the cost of surgeries and treatment, and it will fill the gap of shortage of public hospitals in Lattakia.

Based on the need assessment conducted by DAF, the proposed project will focus on the following activities: 

-Provision of life-sustaining health services by covering the costs of 324 surgical operations to most vulnerable groups who cannot afford (IDPs and host community) 184  of beneficiaries are women and children. The priorities are orthopedic operations and cancer chemical doses for children.) 

- Providing financial support to referral cases and prescriptions (for unavailable medicines in the health center) for 12420 patients
The association health centers can receive patients from AlHamam,AlFied and AlBasah and provide its services for them for free.</narrative>
  </description>
